# Meriter Design System: Volt Obsidian & Light Mode

## 1. Visual north star: “The Kinetic Vault”

Balance **stoic precision** and **kinetic energy**: deep slate structure, **purple** as the kinetic accent. Prefer **surface contrast and soft shadow** over loud borders and decorative gradients.

## 2. Typography

- **Family:** **Manrope** first (`font-sans` in `web/tailwind.config.ts`); fallbacks **Inter**, system UI (`web/src/app/layout.tsx` font link).
- **Headings:** bold / extrabold, **letter-spacing −0.02em** (`h1–h6` in `web/src/app/globals.css` `@layer base`).
- **Body:** regular / medium, **line-height ~1.5** (`body` in `globals.css`).

## 3. Color palette (Tailwind-aligned; implemented as CSS vars)

Implementation: **`web/src/app/globals.css`** — `:root` (light) and `[data-theme="dark"]` (dark) set Daisy `--base-*`, shadcn tokens, and authenticated-shell **`--stitch-*-rgb`** (Tailwind `stitch.*` in `web/tailwind.config.ts`).

### Dark mode (Volt Obsidian)

| Role | Tailwind reference | Notes |
|------|---------------------|--------|
| **Primary surface** | `slate-950` | Darkest plane — **desktop sidebar rail** (`--stitch-sidebar-rgb`). |
| **Secondary / canvas** | `slate-900` | **Main content well** — lighter than the rail (`--stitch-canvas-rgb`). |
| **Cards** | `slate-800` | Panels and cards on the canvas (`--stitch-surface-rgb`). |
| **Nested / elevated** | `slate-700` → `slate-600` | Stepped surfaces (`--stitch-surface2-rgb`, `--stitch-elevated-rgb`). |
| **Accent** | `text-purple-400` / `bg-purple-500` | `--stitch-accent-rgb` / `--stitch-accent2-rgb`, `--primary`. |
| **Text** | `text-slate-100` primary, `text-slate-400` muted | `--stitch-text-rgb`, `--stitch-muted-rgb`. |
| **Borders** | `border-slate-800` | `--stitch-border-rgb`; **minimal** white/`border-white/*` — only where a11y or focus requires. |
| **Shadows** | Purple-tinted depth | e.g. `shadow-[0_20px_50px_rgba(156,72,234,0.1)]` for emphasis cards — use sparingly. |

### Light mode

| Role | Tailwind reference |
|------|---------------------|
| **Background** | `bg-slate-50` primary, **`bg-white` cards** |
| **Accent** | `text-purple-600` / `bg-purple-600` |
| **Text** | `text-slate-900` primary, `text-slate-500` muted |
| **Borders** | `border-slate-200` |
| **Shadows** | `shadow-sm` / `shadow-md` (soft grey) |

**Stitch light:** `--stitch-*-rgb` in `:root` keep canvas/sidebar aligned with slate-50 / white planes; same accent purple-600 scale as `--primary`.

## 4. Layout & spacing

- **Base unit:** 4px (8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64).
- **Radius:** **12px** cards (`rounded-xl`, `--radius`), **~8px** controls where specified, **9999px** only for true chips / compact badges — avoid full pills on full-width primary actions unless spec’d.
- **Shell:** desktop **padding 24px** / mobile **16px**; content **max-width 1280px** where templates use `max-w-*`.
- **Navigation:** desktop **sidebar width 280px** (icons + labels); mobile **bottom bar — 5 tabs** (existing layout).

## 5. UI elements & logic

- **Primary button:** purple background, white label. **Secondary:** slate-800 (dark) / slate-100 (light) surfaces; avoid heavy outlines.
- **Data policy (product):** Russian UI — **«Заслуги»** (not «мериты», not G-MRT). **No** verification badges, **no** online/presence on avatars. **Projects (list/marketing):** title, description, status — **no** raw investment counts unless the screen is investment/admin. **Profile contacts:** email + plaintext “other contacts”.

## 6. Prompt for Cursor / AI

Apply Meriter Design System: **Manrope**. **Dark:** slate-950 **sidebar**, slate-900 **content canvas**, slate-800 **cards**, purple-400/500 accents, slate-800 borders. **Light:** slate-50 / white, purple-600 accents. **Terminology:** «Заслуги» in Russian user copy. **Keep** Profile + Navigation structure. **Avoid** unnecessary borders, gradients, and non-functional metrics.
